The paper discusses the use of context information and prediction tools to optimize network performance, which falls under the category of computer networks and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also mentions the study of patterns and periodicity in human behavior, which could be related to social and information networks (cs.SI). The use of prediction tools and optimization techniques also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the challenges and research directions for next generation networks, which could be related to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
